---

The fields ablaze in morning’s hue,
A canvas vast, a world anew.
Each flower sways in sun’s embrace,
In every petal, love’s sweet grace.

As nature wakes from nighttime’s hold,
Her beauty in each moment told,
In every breath, a promise found,
The joy of life, forever bound.

- Thomas Wilbur
